# Field-test harness (Plan 35) — auth for the UNATTENDED, egress-fenced blind runs.
# Copy this file to `.env` in the SAME directory (test/field-test/.env) and fill in
# ONE of the two credentials below. `.env` is gitignored (repo-root `.gitignore`
# ignores `.env` at any depth) — never commit it.
#
# The nested blind `claude` runs inside a Docker container whose ONLY network
# egress is anthropic.com (an allowlist-proxy sidecar). Whichever credential you
# set is the ONLY one that crosses into the container — nothing else from your
# shell env is passed in. Set BOTH and the subscription token wins.

# --- pick ONE ---------------------------------------------------------------

# (a) Claude subscription. Mint with `claude setup-token` and paste it here.
#     Rounds then draw on your 5-hour subscription windows instead of billing an
#     API key — you pay in throughput rather than dollars, so an unattended round
#     competes with your own interactive usage.
#     NOTE: a subscription token has NO spend cap. FIELD_RUN_BUDGET_MIN below is
#     then the only backstop — consider lowering it for unattended rounds.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# (b) Anthropic API key — pay-per-token. Use a key with a LOW spend cap; an
#     unattended round must never be able to burn your quota.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- optional overrides (uncomment to change a default) ---
# FIELD_MODEL=sonnet          # blind-agent model — Sonnet is the fixed cast (Plan 35)
# FIELD_RUN_BUDGET_MIN=60     # total wall-clock kill for one unattended round (minutes)
# FIELD_N8N_TAG=              # n8n image tag (default: the smoke-suite pin)
